                "TaskName": "EATlong",
                "TaskDescription": "The Effort Allocation Task (EAT) involves participants earning food or money by using a grip force device to move a virtual ball upwards on a screen, keeping it above a red line to score points. It varies by reward type (money or food), reward magnitude (low: 1 point, high: 10 points), and difficulty (60% or 70% of maximum effort). After a training phase (~5 minutes) to determine maximum effort, participants enter the experimental phase (~28 minutes).",
                "Instructions": "You play for money and food by using pressure to move the ball above a red line. You earn points for every full second the ball stays above the line. The exchange rate is 100 money points = 32 cents and 100 food points = 25kcal, and you can convert points to money and snacks afterward. The experiment lasts about 30 minutes.",
                "B0FieldSource": [
                    "phasediff_fmap",
                    "pepolar_fmap0"
