                "TaskName": "ERT",
                "TaskDescription": "The Erotic Rating Task (ERT) contains 60 black-and-white images across three categories: erotic couple, non-erotic positive couple, and non-erotic neutral couple (20 each). Each image appears for 5 seconds, followed by a 0.5-second fixation cross before participants rate their sexual arousal (0–100) via a button box. A randomized inter-trial interval (2–8s, mean 4s) follows. Pseudo-randomization prevents more than two consecutive images from the same category. A practice run with three images precedes the task. Stimuli were pre-validated in an online study of women aged 35–60 (N=96, Age_mean=44.68, Age_SD=7.63).",
                "Instructions": "You will see different images on the screen. Indicate how much each image sexually arouses you by moving the pointer via the left and right buttons and confirming the current position with the middle button. The scale ranges from 'not at all' to 'moderate' to 'very strong'.",
